author: Mark Woodley
title: Iowa jumps to 17th in AP poll, next opponent Northwestern falls
text:
Iowa jumps to 17th in AP poll, next opponent Northwestern falls Posted: The latest news and information on the University of Iowa Hawkeyes sports teams, including football, basketball, volleyball, baseball, softball and more. More >> IOWA CITY (KWWL) - 
The Iowa Hawkeye football team received one of the biggest jumps in the AP college football poll, rising 5 spots from #22 to #17. The move tied for the second largest in the poll this week. Michigan led that category jumping 6 spots to #12. 
Iowa's rise comes on the heels of Saturday's 29-20 win over Illinois which pushed the Hawks to 6-0 for the first time since the 2009 season. 
Northwestern, the Hawkeyes' next opponent, fell 7 spots to #20 following their loss to Michigan. 
Saturday's contest between the Hawkeyes and Wildcats marks the first time that Iowa's played in a contest with both teams ranked since 2010.
